content.description: Bouldery start on polished holds, pull a bulge and jugs to the top, pumpy.
content.protection: 4 bolts(3 of which are spinners), rap hangers
content.location: Right of Bird in hand, first route left of Gotz Crack.

content.description: Obvious crack that splits the face of Wild Iowa Wall. Sees little traffic.
content.protection: Gear, If top roping, there are trees on top for anchor, or climb Hungry or Hot Tamale and use their anchors to top rope.
content.location: The crack coming from the cave between Hot Tomale on  the left, and Hungry on the right.

climbs.name: Crack to the right of Atropine

content.description: Crack has some hand jams and each side has pockets and edges for easy hand and foot holds.  The ledge you take exiting the crack can be muddy.  There is little protection until you get from there to the tree.
content.location:
This is the crack to the right of Atropine. 

  There is an easy walk-off to the left.

content.description: One of the more popular climbs on Wild Iowa Wall, steep pocket pulling!
content.protection: 3 bolts to rap hangers (the left hanger is a spinner)
content.location: 5th route from the left. From Gotz Crack second route to the right. Look for a good sized jug that has been epoxied back on.

content.description:
short one or two move wonder, after the first bolt this is a 5.8 

  Alternate start aka "Atropine Direct"   Start to the left of the last two bolts, pull off a right hand on the bottom of the bulge to hit a left hand on the bulge and hit a bucket over the bulge, continue straight up to end just to the left of the anchors. Either stick clip the first bolt (because you can't reach it) or hang on till the second. 

  most climb the line starting under the first bolt going up over the bulge.
lots of bad 2 finger pockets, the grade can be disputed.
somewhat polished, grade is more consistant than Atropine
From my observations, the difficulty of this climb is more consistent than Soul.
content.location: Route to the left of Soul Ignition.
One route left of Bird in Hand.

content.description: Pulling through the first few moves felt the toughest, after that it's a really nice jug haul that flowed up the wall on bomber limestone. I can't believe this doesn't have bolts on it and the two routes on the far left do...
content.protection: This is a toprope route. There are two good sized trees up top to build your anchors off.
content.location: Just right of the crack to the right of Atropine. Finishes right of the dark blue and gold streak.

content.description: Route shares rap hangers with Wild Iowa.
content.protection: 2 bolts, rap hangers(same as Wild Iowa).
content.location: 2nd route from the left, right of Wild Iowa.

content.description: Make the clip on the second bolt, breathe and finish it.
content.location: Third from the right. Left of Virgin, crack and cave to the left.

content.description: Shady when there is tree coverage, can by busy. Good collection of short overhanging routes(5.10a -5.12a) close to the parking lot.
